WEBVTT

00:01.058 --> 00:02.680
Hey there and welcome to Soul Church.

00:03.301 --> 00:07.107
Our prayer is that this message encourages you wherever you may be in life.

00:07.708 --> 00:12.715
We've been hearing so many stories about what God is doing in people's lives and we'd love to hear yours.

00:13.056 --> 00:17.582
So take a second and send your story to stories at soulchurch.com.

00:17.602 --> 00:21.648
Thanks again for joining us today and we hope that you enjoy the message.

00:22.069 --> 00:22.570
God bless.

00:24.252 --> 00:25.795
Are you ready for the Word of God?

00:27.637 --> 00:28.178
Today.

00:28.802 --> 00:36.769
On mission, Matthew 2819, go and make disciples of all nations, baptize Him in the name of the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit.

00:37.670 --> 00:40.153
Last week, I just want to commend Waiisha.

00:40.193 --> 00:41.814
Don't shrink back.

00:42.054 --> 00:43.496
Well done, amazing word.

00:44.497 --> 00:45.277
Where's Waiisha?

00:45.297 --> 00:45.938
Is she somewhere?

00:47.419 --> 00:48.300
Well done, Waiisha.

00:48.320 --> 00:52.464
I like when she said, obedience before understanding.

00:53.145 --> 00:54.306
What a challenging thought.

00:54.446 --> 00:54.906
So thank you.

00:54.966 --> 00:58.770
Father, we just come around your word today with great expectation.

00:59.394 --> 01:01.997
Speak to us, Holy Spirit.

01:02.017 --> 01:02.318
Amen.

01:04.180 --> 01:05.481
We all have desires.

01:07.123 --> 01:15.333
We might not even realize it, but we all have a longing to feel a sense of worth, a sense of purpose, and a sense of belonging.

01:16.335 --> 01:25.586
But one of the greatest human desires, especially as you get older, is legacy, leading a legacy for when we're gone.

01:26.818 --> 01:28.641
We do this through accomplishments.

01:28.701 --> 01:36.291
We do it for achievements, a name on a wall somewhere, a bench in the park, writing a book, inheritance, all those things.

01:37.233 --> 01:38.615
None of those things are bad things.

01:38.635 --> 01:43.141
They're all positive things, but they're all temporary and they will eventually fade away.

01:43.181 --> 01:52.394
The bench will break, the stone will perish, the inheritance will be spent, and the legacy will disappear.

01:53.896 --> 01:55.218
Our only legacy

01:55.330 --> 01:58.274
which will last forever is God's family.

02:00.237 --> 02:08.489
If we really want to leave a legacy and make an eternal impact on the earth, there's only one way to do it.

02:09.250 --> 02:15.418
To take your notes, we'd write this down, to invite someone to be part of God's family.

02:16.760 --> 02:19.564
To invite someone into God's family.

02:20.906 --> 02:23.570
There's no greater legacy or mission in this life

02:23.746 --> 02:29.095
than bringing somebody into the family of God because that is true legacy.

02:30.678 --> 02:37.109
In the book of Philemon, a tiny little book in the New Testament, Paul writes this letter in prison.

02:38.592 --> 02:42.379
This epistle is written to a wealthy business leader.

02:42.940 --> 02:48.850
He's a Christian and he writes to him about this whole thought about legacy and sharing his faith.

02:49.890 --> 02:54.356
And it says, I thank my God, making mention of you always in my prayers.

02:55.377 --> 02:59.963
Verse five, hearing of your love and faith which you have towards the Lord Jesus and all the saints.

03:00.704 --> 03:08.414
That the sharing of your faith may become effective by the acknowledgement of every good thing which is in you in Christ Jesus.

03:09.275 --> 03:18.066
Now we can read that verse and I've read that verse many times as I've read through the Bible each year, but there is a shift in that verse which we can easily miss.

03:18.498 --> 03:25.365
Because the first part of it, it says this, it says, hearing of your love and faith towards the Lord, hearing.

03:25.886 --> 03:29.250
And then it says in verse thing, that the sharing of your faith.

03:29.991 --> 03:33.755
It talks about hearing and it talks about sharing.

03:34.876 --> 03:39.761
God doesn't just want you and I to have faith, he wants us to share faith.

03:41.003 --> 03:47.890
We come to church on a Sunday, we attend our group, we do discipleship classes and all those things,

03:48.066 --> 03:49.989
We hear good news.

03:50.329 --> 03:51.531
We hear the word of God.

03:51.551 --> 03:54.536
The Bible says, faith comes by hearing and hearing from the word of God.

03:54.556 --> 03:59.643
And Paul, as he writes to Phileme, says, it's good to hear faith.

03:59.663 --> 04:03.689
But a lot of those, it stops there at the hearing phase.

04:04.210 --> 04:07.755
Paul goes on to Phileme and he says, to share faith.

04:08.857 --> 04:15.186
We talked week one about gathering and going, gathering, which is hearing, going, which is sharing.

04:19.298 --> 04:26.947
Having faith, you've never heard me say this before, having faith is not enough as a follower of Christ.

04:26.967 --> 04:27.528
It's not enough.

04:29.110 --> 04:33.616
Paul says the mandate is we have to share it.

04:34.737 --> 04:42.827
Now statistics, if they're right, and even if they're wrong by 10%, this is still a staggering stat.

04:43.828 --> 04:48.434
It says that 95% of Christians have never shared their faith.

04:49.730 --> 04:52.694
Now today you are fueling your faith.

04:52.714 --> 04:55.197
You are in church and who fills up lifted already?

04:55.257 --> 04:57.500
I'm like, I'm like, oh my goodness me.

04:58.401 --> 05:03.387
After spending a long time in the air this week, my faith is filled, I feel fueled.

05:03.427 --> 05:10.796
Paul says it's not enough just to fuel your faith to hear you've actually got to step out and share your faith with others.

05:11.177 --> 05:13.319
You know, we share our sweets, we share our time.

05:13.640 --> 05:18.546
Some of us share our money, but Paul is encouraging Philemon to share his faith.

05:20.930 --> 05:26.457
A lady walked out of church after first service, she said, oh my word, that was a really heavy session, John, so I'm just warning you.

05:27.659 --> 05:30.963
Okay, we're warming up, but this is gonna be a challenging 30 minutes together.

05:31.664 --> 05:35.669
This is gonna be a challenging on mission message.

05:36.770 --> 05:41.256
When was the last time that we shared our faith?

05:42.738 --> 05:46.062
Not fueled our faith, but we shared our faith?

05:47.484 --> 05:49.266
What if someone asked you and I

05:50.114 --> 05:55.121
to share our faith or lead them to Jesus, what would you say?

05:56.423 --> 06:08.882
Someone came up to you at work or at university, at college, and said, I hear you're a Christian, I hear you attend that church, and I would like to know Jesus, and I would like to find Jesus, and I would like to you to share your faith.

06:09.082 --> 06:13.769
What would we do, chat GBT, quickly help?

06:13.789 --> 06:19.538
Call Matt, bring them to church, that's a good option.

06:20.994 --> 06:35.011
But what about if we all felt confident on mission in 2026 to share our faith, not just to fuel our faith, but to share our faith and lead someone personally to Jesus Christ?

06:35.712 --> 06:39.877
Now that's legacy.

06:39.897 --> 06:43.902
Jesus doesn't just save us from something, he sends us to someone.

06:46.685 --> 06:50.450
Jesus saves you so you can introduce someone to the Savior.

06:52.098 --> 06:59.505
Now this is a shift for a lot of us because it's uncomfortable because we've just about come to terms with my word.

06:59.525 --> 07:04.870
I come to church on a Sunday and now you're asking me to share what I'm learning in church with others.

07:05.451 --> 07:05.911
That's right.

07:07.112 --> 07:16.481
I want to talk till around three or four o'clock this afternoon on the title from hearing to sharing, from hearing to sharing.

07:17.122 --> 07:21.426
Last time I spoke, we talked about the why, what God saved us from,

07:21.698 --> 07:22.599
But that's not enough.

07:23.020 --> 07:24.583
He saves us to send us.

07:25.965 --> 07:27.087
He saves us to send us.

07:27.127 --> 07:37.083
The person on the Mission Mandate card, which we filled out two weeks ago, they are waiting for an introduction to Jesus.

07:37.945 --> 07:45.517
The person with the blank space that you pray for every day, it's not just enough to have faith for them.

07:46.839 --> 07:48.562
God wants you to share your faith with them.

07:52.514 --> 07:57.981
Faith comes by hearing, but the gospel is spread by sharing.

07:59.883 --> 08:03.108
Do you know we are one generation from the gospel being extinct in this country?

08:04.509 --> 08:05.130
One generation.

08:06.372 --> 08:13.301
The only thing that will keep it going is sharing, sharing our faith.

08:15.123 --> 08:20.690
Now I know that, I know what Billy Graham taught and I'm a big fan of this, this 10 steps.

08:20.930 --> 08:27.424
Every time you're kind, every time you bless someone, every time you show integrity, you're leading people a little closer to Jesus.

08:28.185 --> 08:29.027
And I love that.

08:30.851 --> 08:33.236
But who would love the opportunity this year?

08:33.256 --> 08:41.874
Who would love it if the Holy Spirit gave you confidence that you didn't just bring someone to church, that you led someone personally to Jesus?

08:46.690 --> 08:50.314
I prayed this crazy prayer at the start of the first, at the end of the last service.

08:50.334 --> 08:51.075
This is my prayer.

08:51.915 --> 08:59.223
Father God, would more people find you outside of the walls of this church this year than inside?

09:02.747 --> 09:03.107
Wow.

09:04.208 --> 09:09.193
Can you imagine if we were in Starbucks or Costa or your coffee house of your choice?

09:11.596 --> 09:12.156
Blue bear?

09:13.197 --> 09:13.938
Greggs?

09:14.658 --> 09:16.640
Nothing wrong with Greg's, best nuggets in the town.

09:17.921 --> 09:23.346
Can you imagine if we just had pockets of salvation breaking out as people were leading others to Christ?

09:28.431 --> 09:30.153
So we talked about the who and the why.

09:30.173 --> 09:37.500
Now this week I want to talk about the how and I want to share really quickly seven steps to help us from moving from hearing to sharing.

09:38.320 --> 09:44.146
Because every week we hear the word of God, but I believe that God is calling us to share the good news.

09:44.866 --> 09:45.948
So these are seven steps.

09:45.968 --> 09:51.596
They're really simple, and I want you to follow them, write them down, and then tomorrow we get to put them into action.

09:51.636 --> 09:58.606
Number one, the first step is to listen to them share their story.

10:00.028 --> 10:01.831
You know our world is desperate for listeners.

10:02.031 --> 10:06.798
Everybody on planet Earth has a deep, deep desire to be listened to.

10:07.559 --> 10:08.901
Have their feelings validated.

10:09.682 --> 10:12.306
Very few people in the world are good listeners.

10:13.698 --> 10:16.823
That's why people pay big money to counselors.

10:17.384 --> 10:25.598
They say 90% of a counselor's job is just to keep eye contact and listen and listen, absorb what they're hearing, to be heard.

10:26.941 --> 10:29.064
Listening builds credibility.

10:29.745 --> 10:31.248
This is mission critical.

10:32.029 --> 10:34.634
When we listen, we become their friend.

10:37.559 --> 10:39.602
You cannot win your enemy to Christ.

10:41.634 --> 10:46.501
They have to become our friends so we can introduce them to a friend of Christ.

10:48.223 --> 10:49.665
People want to be heard.

10:51.628 --> 10:54.812
Before people ask this, is Jesus real?

10:55.273 --> 10:56.294
They ask, are you real?

10:59.178 --> 11:01.061
Before people ask, is soul church real?

11:01.081 --> 11:03.584
They want to know that Chantal and I, we're real.

11:03.644 --> 11:04.565
People want to be heard.

11:05.567 --> 11:06.929
Listening builds trust.

11:07.710 --> 11:10.834
Before people can even think about trusting a book

11:11.042 --> 11:15.428
which is 6,000 years old or more, they want to ask, can you be trusted?

11:16.469 --> 11:17.290
Can I be trusted?

11:20.074 --> 11:22.978
Maybe you say, I don't really have a role at Soul Church.

11:23.078 --> 11:24.600
I never held a microphone.

11:24.620 --> 11:29.206
I've never been asked to lead a service, never been asked to lead a ministry.

11:29.927 --> 11:38.418
I'm asking you to listen, to find someone in your workplace at university who needs Jesus,

11:38.722 --> 11:42.428
And the first step is simply to be a listener.

11:44.591 --> 11:46.895
Buy someone a coffee and listen.

11:48.217 --> 11:53.044
What listening does is listening builds a bridge of love from your heart to their heart.

11:53.324 --> 11:55.267
And then Jesus walks across the bridge.

11:56.970 --> 11:59.053
So when you listen, it connects heart to heart.

11:59.073 --> 12:02.258
And Jesus, the Holy Spirit walks into that conversation.

12:02.914 --> 12:05.076
Romans 12, 13, it says, practice.

12:05.436 --> 12:06.838
Chantel spoke on this two years ago.

12:07.198 --> 12:08.619
Practice hospitality.

12:09.680 --> 12:12.163
Invite people into your life and listen.

12:14.105 --> 12:20.270
You know, we always, we always lead more people to Christ by listening to them and talking to them.

12:22.452 --> 12:24.394
Listening is the key to a person's heart.

12:25.595 --> 12:32.722
So we got to, we got to compiler airport at 2.30 AM on Friday morning.

12:33.186 --> 12:38.292
to catch our flight home, and we went through security, and then it flashed up on the screen.

12:38.452 --> 12:40.155
Flight canceled, no reason.

12:40.175 --> 12:46.362
200 people on a flight, and the one thing I love about you getting there is their customer service.

12:46.743 --> 12:47.363
There wasn't any.

12:48.785 --> 12:49.846
There was no one to talk to.

12:49.907 --> 12:50.888
Everyone's like, well, why didn't you talk?

12:50.908 --> 12:51.709
There's no one to talk to.

12:53.932 --> 13:02.482
So we re-booked our flights home, and flew through Istanbul,

13:02.850 --> 13:09.381
It was amazing because all four of us who were sitting together in Uganda now were now just sitting as individuals across the flight.

13:09.401 --> 13:10.443
And I love the middle aisle.

13:10.463 --> 13:11.525
Anyone loves the middle seat?

13:12.045 --> 13:12.506
It's brilliant.

13:12.546 --> 13:13.127
Six foot two.

13:13.167 --> 13:14.890
And I love being in the middle aisle.

13:15.531 --> 13:17.354
And it's just a pleasure.

13:17.455 --> 13:19.398
It was just an honor to be there.

13:19.418 --> 13:22.443
And justice was down there.

13:22.483 --> 13:23.324
Miracles down there.

13:23.405 --> 13:24.306
And Chantel was

13:24.578 --> 13:25.199
towards the front.

13:25.219 --> 13:26.320
So we were spread out nicely.

13:26.340 --> 13:34.429
And I thought, as a good father, every hour or so, I'll get up and just check on my family, making sure that they're eating the chicken or beef, or whatever meal was on offer.

13:34.970 --> 13:39.856
And Miracle's good, justice was good, they're fast asleep.

13:40.176 --> 13:45.662
And then I went walking to Chantel, and this lady is just gushing her heart.

13:46.523 --> 13:49.807
She's just pouring her heart, and Chantel's like totally engaged.

13:50.588 --> 13:52.530
But you are the Christian of this family.

13:53.346 --> 13:54.567
You are totally saved.

13:55.328 --> 13:56.449
I'm getting back to my movie.

13:56.630 --> 14:02.316
Anyway, I'm like, wow, this lady's hit jackpot sitting next to Chantal for seven hours.

14:06.520 --> 14:07.381
I'll come back to that.

14:09.503 --> 14:12.326
If I want to ask you this, do you know your Amazon driver's name?

14:14.168 --> 14:15.410
Do you know your postman's name?

14:15.430 --> 14:16.631
Do you know your children's name?

14:17.192 --> 14:18.333
Do we stop and listen?

14:18.994 --> 14:23.058
I was challenged over Christmas to make sure I'm listening

14:23.778 --> 14:32.932
Postman had been coming around for a few months, and he docked on the door of the box at Christmas and said, come in, let's have a drink in a mince pie.

14:33.312 --> 14:34.134
He said, are you sure?

14:34.174 --> 14:35.075
I'm really sure.

14:35.416 --> 14:40.824
So I bring him in on a Saturday morning, we're sitting there having some food together, and Chantal comes down and they're dressing down.

14:40.904 --> 14:44.029
I forgot to tell her the Postman was in the kitchen.

14:45.130 --> 14:47.474
She's like, morning, morning.

14:48.235 --> 14:52.882
Anyway, we talked, and he would tell me a little bit about his journey to becoming Postman.

14:53.090 --> 14:55.993
and he left and she was like, what was that all about?

14:56.013 --> 14:57.575
I said, I'm trying to be a good pastor.

14:57.595 --> 15:01.619
I'm trying to be... Do you remember the old days we just invite everyone in?

15:01.659 --> 15:03.061
It's just like, come on, open home.

15:04.983 --> 15:11.570
You know, the challenge in all this is the busyness of life we can forget that everyone has a story.

15:12.511 --> 15:13.472
Everyone is on a journey.

15:15.915 --> 15:18.718
When you listen to the long enough, here's what happens naturally next.

15:18.798 --> 15:21.781
Number two is, number one, you listen to them share their story.

15:21.821 --> 15:22.482
Number two,

15:22.882 --> 15:26.286
You share with them your story, your story.

15:27.827 --> 15:30.931
As we start with listening, share your story.

15:30.971 --> 15:32.472
By the way, you don't have to get the Bible out yet.

15:32.532 --> 15:34.194
Some of you are like, when does the Bible come into it?

15:34.214 --> 15:34.495
Not yet.

15:35.796 --> 15:36.897
Take them to your story.

15:37.778 --> 15:41.202
Not just your story about how you graduated from university.

15:41.823 --> 15:46.968
Talk to them about your story, about how God redeemed your life.

15:47.589 --> 15:50.091
Talk about the goodness of the Lord.

15:50.732 --> 15:52.434
So on my second trip around,

15:52.546 --> 15:54.410
TK132 in the middle of the night.

15:54.430 --> 16:00.422
I checked on the kids all good and then I go back and do you know what's happening?

16:01.003 --> 16:03.929
Chantel is telling this lady her story.

16:04.991 --> 16:06.354
Now she's fallen even more.

16:06.690 --> 16:20.686
She entails tearing up, I'm like, oh my word, she's telling her about the challenges, the abuse, the emotion that she'd been for as a little girl, but she was telling about how God redeemed her, God has saved her, and that light is stronger than darkness, how she'd been through so many things.

16:20.926 --> 16:22.588
She told this lady her story.

16:28.915 --> 16:31.958
Tell people what your life was like before you encountered Jesus.

16:32.319 --> 16:35.122
Who would say that your BC life is worth telling people?

16:36.226 --> 16:37.908
Who's got a BC before Christ's life?

16:39.109 --> 16:40.411
Come on, you all have.

16:42.613 --> 16:45.116
Whose life was a little bit of a, what should we say?

16:46.358 --> 16:47.759
Rocky, good word.

16:48.480 --> 16:49.761
Who had a rocky BC?

16:54.607 --> 16:57.310
John's gospel tells how Jesus healed a blind man.

16:57.831 --> 17:04.338
The hostile leaders keep questioning about questioning Jesus about this man who's regained his sight, and this is what

17:04.706 --> 17:05.847
This is what the man said.

17:05.907 --> 17:07.389
He said, one thing I do know.

17:07.449 --> 17:09.211
I don't know everything, but I do know this.

17:09.691 --> 17:12.895
I was blind, but now I see.

17:12.935 --> 17:14.356
I don't know your story.

17:14.437 --> 17:22.525
I don't know what's happened to you, but one thing I do know and one thing I know about my own life is I was blind, but now I see.

17:22.826 --> 17:24.247
People will argue theology.

17:24.507 --> 17:26.730
People are gonna ask you why bad things happen to good people.

17:26.990 --> 17:32.076
People are gonna throw every question in the book at you, but there's one thing that they cannot argue with.

17:32.476 --> 17:34.258
It is I was blind.

17:34.338 --> 17:36.040
But now I see.

17:36.260 --> 17:40.083
You're looking at a kid from Ty even with four GCSEs, one and a bit A levels.

17:40.404 --> 17:43.507
I was blind, but now I see.

17:45.228 --> 17:47.891
Everyone in this room, you have a story of God's redemption power.

17:48.491 --> 17:51.835
Listen to their story and share your story.

17:52.495 --> 17:58.140
If God helped you through loss and grief, that's your story.

17:58.161 --> 18:01.364
Listen to them share their story, share with them your story.

18:01.404 --> 18:03.986
Number three, tell them Jesus' story.

18:05.922 --> 18:11.669
Matthew, Mark 16, 15, wherever you go in the world, tell everyone the good news.

18:13.071 --> 18:14.252
I love that word wherever.

18:14.953 --> 18:18.177
God's not asking us to make a special trip to tell people about Jesus.

18:18.818 --> 18:31.473
He just says, wherever you are, whether you're an asdah rolling back the prizes, Tesco's where every little helps, wherever you go, tell people about God's story.

18:31.493 --> 18:35.218
We have a duty as a believer in Christ, not just to hear,

18:35.842 --> 18:36.443
but to share.

18:37.565 --> 18:41.090
Some of you are really good at hearing and you are, you're a good student.

18:41.110 --> 18:49.903
You come every week and you take notes and you listen to the pastor and you listen to the teachers every week, but the challenges as Paul said to Philemon, do you share or do you just hear?

18:51.345 --> 18:52.947
The gospel needs to be shared.

18:54.970 --> 18:55.792
What do we tell people?

18:55.852 --> 19:01.040
We tell people to Corinthians 5, 17, if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation.

19:01.941 --> 19:05.426
The old has passed away, behold all things.

19:05.570 --> 19:06.351
have become new.

19:06.711 --> 19:07.913
I don't know your story.

19:08.053 --> 19:09.234
I don't know what you've been through.

19:09.494 --> 19:10.556
I don't know your addiction.

19:10.616 --> 19:12.358
I don't know the crime that you've been involved in.

19:12.458 --> 19:14.340
I don't know the things that have been said over you.

19:14.360 --> 19:18.044
But I do know that when you come into Christ, you are a new creation.

19:18.304 --> 19:21.668
He wipes the slate clean and he gives you a brand new stuff.

19:21.888 --> 19:24.832
When you're talking to people, you share God's story.

19:26.093 --> 19:29.057
And a new creation, that's not self-help.

19:29.817 --> 19:31.199
That's resurrection power.

19:32.901 --> 19:33.842
A lot of people have

19:34.050 --> 19:43.007
Talk to me recently about the power of the universe and the positive energy and the positive vibes that they feel when they come in to Soul Church.

19:43.468 --> 19:46.133
It is not positive energy which is in this room.

19:46.354 --> 19:52.605
It is the power and the redemptive power of the Holy Spirit that is at work in your life.

19:54.950 --> 19:57.074
The universe is a creation.

19:57.506 --> 19:58.387
Not a Savior.

19:58.648 --> 20:02.073
The earth cannot save you and the earth cannot heal you.

20:02.393 --> 20:03.755
God is the healer.

20:03.775 --> 20:05.017
God is the Creator.

20:07.681 --> 20:11.207
Stop worshipping creation and start worshipping the Creator.

20:12.449 --> 20:14.812
People are obsessed and have got it the wrong way around.

20:15.073 --> 20:17.036
We need to be good stewards of God's planet.

